In [ ]:
city_Hotel=0
resort_hotel=0
for i in range(len(df)):
    if df.iloc[i]['hotel']=="Resort Hotel":
        if df.iloc[i]["stays_in_weekend_nights"]>0:
            resort_hotel=resort_hotel+1
    else:
        if df.iloc[i]["stays_in_weekend_nights"]>0:
            city_Hotel=city_Hotel+1
RH=(resort_hotel,city_Hotel)
x=pd.DataFrame(RH).rename(columns={0:"count weekend nights"},index={0:"resort hotel",1:"city hotel"})
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
sns.barplot(x=x.index,y=x['count weekend nights']);

People prefer to choose City Hotel over Resort Hotel over Week and Weekend Nights

In [41]:
single=0
couple=0
family=0
for i in range(len(df)):   
    if (df.loc[i]['adults']==2) & (df.loc[i]['children']==0) & (df.loc[i]['babies']==0) :
        couple=couple+1
        df["family_type"]="couple"
    elif (df.loc[i]['adults']==1) & (df.loc[i]['children']==0) & (df.loc[i]['babies']==0):
        single=single+1
        df["family_type"]="single"
    elif (df.loc[i]['adults'])+((df.loc[i]['children'])+(df.loc[i]['babies']>2)):
        family=family+1
        df["family_type"]="family"
    
print(single,couple,family)

d3 = pd.concat([d1,d2], axis = 1)
